The paper discusses the concept of service shifting in the context of 5G network orchestration, which involves the management and allocation of network resources to different services. This falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the challenges and benefits of service shifting, which can be seen as a system-level issue (cs.SY) and a data center management problem (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of service shifting on security and reliability, which relates to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and augmented reality (cs.AR).
